%N A394903 Number of square grid edges that are visible through the n-th order Sierpinski carpet fractal.
%C A394903 This sequence is obtained by exactly overlaying the n-th iteration of the Sierpinski carpet fractal (with the 0th iteration being a square patch with no holes) on a 3^n X 3^n square grid, and then counting the number of grid edges which are not covered.
%H A394903 Wikipedia, <a href="https://wikipedia.org/wiki/Sierpinski_carpet">Sierpinski carpet</a>.
%F A394903 a(n) = 8*a(n-1) + 2*(3^(2*(n-1)) - 3^(n-1)) for n>0; a(0) = 0.
%e A394903 At n=2 (the third term in the sequence), we exactly overlay the Sierpinski carpet on a 9 by 9 square grid, and observe that all edges of the grid are covered except for the 12 edges which are visible through the center hole of the Sierpinski carpet.
%e A394903 At n=3, there are 144 visible grid edges in the center hole plus 12 visible edges in each of the 8 smaller holes that surround the center hole, and so on.
%o A394903 (PARI) a(n) = if (n<=1, 0, 8*a(n-1) + 2*(3^(2*(n-1)) - 3^(n-1))); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Apr 07 2026
%Y A394903 Cf. A153490, A293143.
